{"key":"processedPost-11478917","value":{"id":11478917,"first":11473473,"last":11483023,"when":1258579460,"utime":"11/18/09 11:24 PM","content":"Your ratio is fine, but pasteurization occurs when the substrate temperature is maintained at 140F/60C for 90 minutes.&nbsp; If you use a 160F oven, it might take 12 hours or longer for the substrate to heat to that temperature.&nbsp; I'd suggest putting the substrate into bags or jars and heating them in a pot of water on the stove.&nbsp; You can see an example of it done that way in video format on my website in the horse manure or casing tek.<br />RR","title":"Re: Coir mix and pasteurize ?'s"}}